{"lemma":"حِيلَةُ","slug":"حِيلَةُ","root":"ح.#.ل","root_slug":"ح-_-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-_-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حِيلَة","root":"حول","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9590","n9786","n9785"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"trick, artifice, maneuver","examples":[{"text":"إِلَّا ٱلْمُسْتَضْعَفِينَ مِنَ ٱلرِّجَالِ وَٱلنِّسَاءِ وَٱلْوِلْدَانِ لَا يَسْتَطِيعُونَ حِيلَةً وَلَا يَهْتَدُونَ سَبِيلًا"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shift"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"means to an end"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dodge"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare حَاوَلَ (ḥāwala, “to try, to deceive by artifice”)."},"ipa":["/ħiː.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9590","headword_ar":"حِيلَةٌ","root":"Hwl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K, &c.,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiwolapN","text_ar":"حِوْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Er-Rághib, TA,) [said to be an inf. n., (see 8,)] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawolN","text_ar":"حَوْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayolN","text_ar":"حَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiwalN","text_ar":"حِوَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) which is also a pl. of the first, (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawolapN","text_ar":"حَوْلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuwlapN","text_ar":"حُولَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawiylN","text_ar":"حَوِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAy^ilapN","text_ar":"حَايِلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 652) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAlapN","text_ar":"مَحَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAlN","text_ar":"مَحَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) [said to be an inf. n., (see 8,)] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHiylapN","text_ar":"مَحِيلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiHotiyaAlN","text_ar":"اِحْتِيَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHaw~ulN","text_ar":"تَحَوُّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHay~ulN","text_ar":"تَحَيُّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K; [see 8;]) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of changing from one state to another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of shifting from one thing to another;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiylapN","text_ar":"حِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolapN","text_ar":"فِعْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAla","text_ar":"حَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jilosapN","text_ar":"جِلْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasa","text_ar":"جَلَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHaw~ulN","text_ar":"تَحَوُّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAla","text_ar":"حَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (see what follows;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means, of evading"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eluding a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of effecting an object; an evasion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elusion, a shift, a wile, an artifice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"artful contrivance"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"device, a machination, a trick, a plot, a stratagem,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an expedient;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a means of effecting one's transition from that which he dislikes to that which he likes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT, in explanation of the first word;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"art, artifice, cunning, ingenuity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the management of affairs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turning over,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revolving, thoughts, ideas, schemes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contrivances, in the mind, so as to find a way of attaining one's object;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellence of consideration"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deliberation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability to manage according to one's own free will,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with subtilty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) accord. to Er-Rághib,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiylapN","text_ar":"حِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a means of attaining to some state concealedly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is mostly used of that in which is sin, or offence, or disobedience; but sometimes of that in the exercise of which is wisdom; and hence God is described as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adiydu","text_ar":"شَدِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaHaAli","text_ar":"المَحَالِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong in attaining, concealedly from men, to that in which is wisdom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Abu-l-Bakà, it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aHaw~ulu","text_ar":"التَّحَوُّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; because by it one shifts from one state to another, by a species of forecast, and gentleness, or delicacy, so as to change a thing from its outward appearance: (TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiylapN","text_ar":"حِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiwalN","text_ar":"حِوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiyalN","text_ar":"حِيَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which latter is the most common form, and also, as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiwalN","text_ar":"حِوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said to be syn. with the sing.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiylaAtN","text_ar":"حِيلَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA Hiylapa lahu","text_ar":"لَا حِيلَةَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has no mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means, of evading"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA biyadiY HiylapN","text_ar":"مَا بِيَدِى حِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have no mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means, of evading"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almaro'u yaEojizu laA maHaAlapa","text_ar":"المَرْءُ يَعْجِزُ لَا مَحَالَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Man becomes impotent: there is no avoiding"},{"kind":"text","text":"it]. (S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohu","text_ar":"مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA maHaAlapa","text_ar":"لَا مَحَالَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA bud~a","text_ar":"لَا بُدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no avoiding it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"escaping it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, * K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almawotu A=tK","text_ar":"المَوْتُ ا=تٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA maHaAlapa","text_ar":"لَا مَحَالَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Death comes: there is no avoiding"},{"kind":"text","text":"it]. (S.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiwalN","text_ar":"حِوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuwlapN","text_ar":"حُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b3-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawolN","text_ar":"حَوْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu AlHiyali","text_ar":"عِلْمُ الحِيَلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The science of mechanics."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Ks","TA","Sgh","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n9786","headword_ar":"حِيلَةٌ","root":"Hyl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayolN","text_ar":"حَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", above; and see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hwl","text_ar":"حول"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n9785","headword_ar":"حَيْلَةٌ","root":"Hyl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A large number of goats:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a herd of goats:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a flock of sheep."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stones rolled down from the side of a mountain to its bottom until they become many:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an overhanging mass of rock that falls down from the head of a mountain to its bottom."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l-Mekárim, O.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayolN","text_ar":"حَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}